Moved processing of HostComponentExtension to parse2 which is after the swcs have been added to the symbol table.
This allows the HostComponentExtension to accurately determine if the class already has a hostComponent property.
Changed HostComponentExtension to update binding information if a hostComponent property is injected into a class.
HostComponentExtension processing should not be done in parse1 because getting the classInfo for a class during parse1
will polute the symbol table when an ancestor class is defined in a swc.  The poluted symbol table then causes the
BindableSecondPassEvaluator to assume the class does not already implement IEventDispatcher.
